title: Grateful Dead Live at Greek Theatre, U. Of California on 1989-08-18
description: Cold Rain & Snow, Minglewood Blues, Row Jimmy, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Built To Last, Victim Or The Crime, Bird Song, Promised Land Iko Iko, Looks Like Rain, Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam-> Crazy Fingers-> I Need A Miracle-> Stella Blue-> Throwing Stones-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Black Muddy River, E: We Bid You Good Night

reviews.review_text: Better levels OK, I think this version sounds best, based on the needed increase in levels across the board......great show, thanks!!!!
Oh Yeah Sound is great, and I Know You Rider is very nice.
Nice re-master!!! This is the pick of the litter for this show on the Archive......more wind in it's proverbial sail than the other (still great) uploads.....

Stella Blue Sounds So Good Not a fabulous outing by the band , but good enough to please. Truly remarkable about this particular show is that the bass sounds like a Mack Truck in your living room.

Jerry's solo in Stella is very inspired.

Merits 5 stars due to superior recording and remastering.
quality good sound quality,good set list 4 stars
IWT! i was there! walked to and from the show from my old house on milky way and derby
